msgstr "Monks’ Confession 41"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "41. Acelakasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on naked ascetics"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.91"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.41.1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.41.1.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.347"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa866"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Vesālī in the hall with the peaked "
"roof in the Great Wood."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena saṃghassa khādanīyaṃ ussannaṃ hoti."
msgstr "At that time the Order was receiving an abundance of non-staple food."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.1.3"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "Venerable Ānanda told the Master, who said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.1.4"
msgid "“Tenahānanda, vighāsādānaṃ pūvaṃ dehī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, Ānanda, give the biscuits to those who take leftovers.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.1.5"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paṭissuṇitvā vighāsāde "
"paṭipāṭiyā nisīdāpetvā ekekaṃ pūvaṃ dento aññatarissā paribbājikāya ekaṃ "
"maññamāno dve pūve adāsi."
msgstr ""
"“Yes, Venerable Sir.” Ānanda got them to sit in a row and gave them one "
"biscuit each, until he accidentally gave two to a female wanderer."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.1.6"
msgid "Sāmantā paribbājikāyo taṃ paribbājikaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "The female wanderers sitting next to her said to her,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.1.7"
msgid "“jāro te eso samaṇo”ti."
msgstr "“This ascetic is your lover.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.1.8"
msgid "“Na me so samaṇo jāro, ekaṃ maññamāno dve pūve adāsī”ti."
msgstr "“He’s not. He gave me two, thinking they were one.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.1.9"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho … pe …"
msgstr "And a second time …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.1.10"
msgid ""
"tatiyampi kho āyasmā ānando ekekaṃ pūvaṃ dento tassāyeva paribbājikāya ekaṃ "
"maññamāno dve pūve adāsi."
msgstr ""
"And a third time Ānanda gave them one biscuit each, until he accidentally "
"gave two to that same female wanderer."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.1.11"
msgid "Sāmantā paribbājikāyo taṃ paribbājikaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "Once again the female wanderers sitting next to her said to her,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.1.12"
msgid "“jāro te eso samaṇo”ti."
msgstr "“This ascetic is your lover.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.1.13"
msgid "“Na me so samaṇo jāro, ekaṃ maññamāno dve pūve adāsī”ti."
msgstr "“He’s not. He gave me two, thinking they were one.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.1.14"
msgid "“Jāro na jāro”ti bhaṇḍiṃsu."
msgstr "And they started to argue about whether or not they were lovers."

#. </p><p><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.41.1.2"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.2.1"
msgid "Aññataropi ājīvako parivesanaṃ agamāsi."
msgstr "A certain Ājīvaka ascetic, too, went to that distribution of food."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.2.2"
msgid ""
"Aññataro bhikkhu pahūtena sappinā odanaṃ madditvā tassa ājīvakassa mahantaṃ "
"piṇḍaṃ adāsi."
msgstr ""
"A monk mixed rice with a large amount of ghee and gave him a large lump."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.348"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.2.3"
msgid "Atha kho so ājīvako taṃ piṇḍaṃ ādāya agamāsi."
msgstr "He took it and left."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.2.4"
msgid "Aññataro ājīvako taṃ ājīvakaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "Another Ājīvaka asked him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.2.5"
msgid "“kuto tayā, āvuso, piṇḍo laddho”ti?"
msgstr "“Where did you get that lump?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.2.6"
msgid ""
"“Tassāvuso, samaṇassa gotamassa muṇḍagahapatikassa parivesanāya laddho”ti."
msgstr ""
"“From the food distribution of the ascetic Gotama, that shaven-headed lay "
"person.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.92"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa867"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.2.7"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho upāsakā tesaṃ ājīvakānaṃ imaṃ kathāsallāpaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Some lay followers overheard that conversation between those Ājīvaka "
"ascetics."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.2.8"
msgid "Atha kho te upāsakā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
msgstr "They then approached the Master,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.2.9"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu."
msgstr "bowed down to him, sat down to one side,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.2.10"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te upāsakā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.2.11"
msgid ""
"“ime, bhante, titthiyā avaṇṇakāmā buddhassa avaṇṇakāmā dhammassa avaṇṇakāmā "
"saṃghassa."
msgstr ""
"“Venerable Sir, these ascetics of other sects want to disparage the Buddha, "
"the Teaching, and the Order."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.2.12"
msgid "Sādhu, bhante, ayyā titthiyānaṃ sahatthā na dadeyyun”ti."
msgstr ""
"It would be good, Venerable Sir, if the monks didn’t give anything to the "
"ascetics of other sects from their own hands.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.2.13"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā te upāsake dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi "
"samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi."
msgstr ""
"After the Master had instructed, inspired, and gladdened those lay followers "
"with a teaching,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.2.14"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te upāsakā bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā samādapitā "
"samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ "
"katvā pakkamiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"they rose from their seats, bowed down to the him, circumambulated him with "
"their right side towards him, and left."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.2.15"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā "
"bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.2.16"
msgid ""
"“tena hi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññapessāmi dasa atthavase "
"paṭicca—"
msgstr ""
"“Well then, monks, I will lay down a training rule for the following ten "
"reasons:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.2.17"
msgid ""
"saṃghasuṭṭhutāya, saṃghaphāsutāya … pe … saddhammaṭṭhitiyā, vinayānuggahāya."
msgstr ""
"for the well-being of the Order,  for the comfort of the Order, for the "
"restraint of bad people, for the ease of well-behaved monks, for the "
"restraint of corruptions in the present life, for avoiding corruptions in "
"future lives, to give rise to confidence in those without it, to increase "
"the confidence of those who have it, for the continuation of the true "
"Teaching, and for supporting the training."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.2.18"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.2.18a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa868"></a>
#. <span class="rule">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.2.19"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu acelakassa vā paribbājakassa vā paribbājikāya vā sahatthā "
"khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā dadeyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk gives staple or non-staple food to a naked ascetic, to a male "
"wanderer, or to a female wanderer with his own hands, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession.’”"

#. </span>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs1.2.20"
msgid "(<em>41</em>:<strong>90</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.41.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.41.2.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.349"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa869"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa870"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.1.6"
msgid "Acelako nāma"
msgstr "A naked ascetic:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.1.7"
msgid "yo koci paribbājakasamāpanno naggo."
msgstr "whatever wanderer is naked."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa871"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.1.8"
msgid "Paribbājako nāma"
msgstr "A male wanderer:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.1.9"
msgid "bhikkhuñca sāmaṇerañca ṭhapetvā yo koci paribbājakasamāpanno."
msgstr "any wanderer apart from Buddhist monks and novice monks."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa872"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.1.10"
msgid "Paribbājikā nāma"
msgstr "A female wanderer:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.1.11"
msgid ""
"bhikkhuniñca sikkhamānañca sāmaṇeriñca ṭhapetvā yā kāci paribbājikasamāpannā."
msgstr ""
"any female wanderer apart from Buddhist nuns, trainee nuns, and novice nuns."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa873"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.1.12"
msgid "Khādanīyaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Non-staple food:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.1.13"
msgid "pañca bhojanāni—udakadantaponaṃ ṭhapetvā avasesaṃ khādanīyaṃ nāma."
msgstr ""
"apart from the five staple foods, water, and tooth-cleaners, the rest is "
"called “non-staple food.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa874"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.1.14"
msgid "Bhojanīyaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Staple food:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.1.15"
msgid "pañca bhojanāni—"
msgstr "there are five kinds of staple food:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.1.16"
msgid "odano, kummāso, sattu, maccho, maṃsaṃ."
msgstr "cooked grain, porridge, flour, fish, and meat."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa875"></a>
#. <span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.1.17"
msgid "Dadeyyāti"
msgstr "Gives:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.1.18"
msgid ""
"kāyena vā kāyapaṭibaddhena vā nissaggiyena vā deti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"if he gives by body or by what is connected to the body or by releasing, he "
"commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </span>
#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.41.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa876"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.2.1"
msgid ""
"Titthiye titthiyasaññī sahatthā khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā deti, āpatti "
"pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an ascetic from another sect, and he perceives it as an ascetic "
"from another sect, and he gives them staple or non-staple food with his own "
"hands, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.2.2"
msgid ""
"Titthiye vematiko sahatthā khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā deti, āpatti "
"pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an ascetic from another sect, but he is unsure if it is, and he "
"gives them staple or non-staple food with his own hands, he commits an "
"offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.2.3"
msgid ""
"Titthiye atitthiyasaññī sahatthā khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā deti, āpatti "
"pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is an ascetic from another sect, but he does not perceive it as an "
"ascetic from another sect, and he gives them staple or non-staple food with "
"his own hands, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa877"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.2.4"
msgid "Udakadantaponaṃ deti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he gives water or tooth-cleaners, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.2.5"
msgid "Atitthiye titthiyasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is not an ascetic from another sect, but he perceives it as an ascetic "
"from another sect, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.2.6"
msgid "Atitthiye vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is not an ascetic from another sect, but he is unsure of it, he "
"commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.2.7"
msgid "Atitthiye atitthiyasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If it is not an ascetic from another sect, and he does not perceive it as an "
"ascetic from another sect, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.41.2.3"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.350"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa878"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.3.2"
msgid "dāpeti na deti,"
msgstr "if he does not give, but gets it given;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.3.3"
msgid "upanikkhipitvā deti,"
msgstr "if he gives by placing it near the person;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.3.4"
msgid "bāhirālepaṃ deti,"
msgstr "if he gives ointments for external use;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.3.5"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.3.6"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa879"></a>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc41:pts-cs2.3.7"
msgid "Acelakasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr "The first rule, the training rule on naked ascetics, is finished."

